          <title>This German church is the tallest in the world. Until Spain's La Sagrada Familia is done, anyway</title>
          <description><![CDATA[ULM, Germany (AP) — The Ulmer Münster in southern Germany is the world's tallest church. For now, anyway. The Gothic-style Lutheran church's reign — begun in May 31, 1890 — could end in 2025, when La Sagrada Familia Basilica's “Tower of Jesus Christ” in Spain is set to be completed.]]></description>
